## Layer 1: WAF Rate Limits (CloudFront Edge)

**Files:** `terraform/infra/waf.tf` and `terraform/prod/waf.tf` (in the frontend repo)

| Priority | Rule Name | Rate Limit | Scope | Protects |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `rsvp-rate-limit` | 10 req / 5 min per IP | Body contains `rsvpViaEventLink` | Public RSVP submissions |
| 2 | `registration-rate-limit` | 10 req / 5 min per IP | Body contains `registerUser` | Account creation |
| 3 | `login-rate-limit` | 10 req / 5 min per IP | Body contains `Login` | Authentication |
| 4 | `create-event-rate-limit` | 20 req / 5 min per IP | Body contains `createEvent` | Event creation |
| 5 | `view-tracking-rate-limit` | 10 req / 5 min per IP | Body contains `recordInvitationView` OR `recordPublicLinkView` | View tracking (INV-212) |
| 6 | `blanket-graphql-rate-limit` | 100 req / 1 min per IP | ALL `/graphql` POST requests | Catch-all for unlisted operations |

### WAF Rule Pattern

All WAF rules follow the same structure:
- `rate_based_statement` with `aggregate_key_type = "IP"`
- `scope_down_statement` using `byte_match_statement` on the POST body
- `CONTAINS` matching on the GraphQL operation name
- Block action returns **429** (not 403) with JSON error body matching GraphQL error format
- `Retry-After: 300` header
- CloudWatch metrics enabled for monitoring

### Adding a New WAF Rule

1. Add the rule block to BOTH `terraform/infra/waf.tf` and `terraform/prod/waf.tf`
2. Use the next available priority number
3. Bump the blanket rule priority to stay last
4. Match on the GraphQL `operationName` in the POST body
5. Use `or_statement` if multiple operations share the same limit
6. Run `terraform plan` to verify, then `terraform apply`

