## Layer 3: Database Idempotency (PostgreSQL)

These are not "rate limits" per se, but they provide the final data integrity guarantee:

| Operation | SQL Guard | Effect |
|---|---|---|
| `setFirstViewedAt` | `WHERE first_viewed_at IS NULL` | Only the first write succeeds; subsequent writes are no-ops |
| `incrementPublicLinkViewCount` | `SET count = count + 1` | Atomic increment, no lost updates under concurrency |
| Unique constraints | `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` / `UNIQUE` indexes | Prevents duplicate records |

