## Monitoring & Observability

### WAF Metrics (CloudWatch)

Each WAF rule has `cloudwatch_metrics_enabled = true`. Monitor:
- `hestia-{env}-rsvp-rate-limit` — RSVP abuse attempts
- `hestia-{env}-registration-rate-limit` — Registration spam
- `hestia-{env}-login-rate-limit` — Brute force login attempts
- `hestia-{env}-view-tracking-rate-limit` — View tracking abuse
- `hestia-{env}-blanket-graphql-rate-limit` — General API abuse

### Application Logging

Rate limiters log at these levels:
- `INFO` on initialization: config values, max requests, window size
- `DEBUG` when a request is rate-limited: key (truncated), limit hit
- `WARN` when IP is null (rate limiting bypassed/dropped)
- `WARN` for invalid UUIDs (potential scanning/abuse)

### Structured Log Pattern

```
VIEW_TRACK rate-limited: inv=cc120212... ip=a1b2c3d4 (first 8 chars of hash)
VIEW_TRACK clientIp is null — dropping request for inv=cc120212...
VIEW_TRACK invalid invitation UUID: not-a-uuid
```

