## Known Limitations

1. **In-memory rate limiters reset on deploy** — a deploy creates a brief window where all limits are refreshed. WAF provides continuity during this window.
2. **WAF minimum window is 5 minutes** — cannot enforce sub-5-minute windows at the edge.
3. **WAF cannot rate-limit per resource** — only per IP. An attacker sending unique resource IDs from one IP is caught by WAF, but an attacker sending the same resource ID from many IPs is only caught by the app-level limiter.
4. **IP rotation bypasses both WAF and app rate limiters** — distributed attacks with many IPs are not fully mitigated. DB idempotency is the final defense.
5. **Mobile native session dedup is deferred** (INV-215) — `sessionStorage` guard only works on web. Native apps may re-fire mutations on component remount.
